{"_id":"EAATan01","name":"Automata Records","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Ancient","excerpt":"Spend a Slow Action to tap into the machine's databases. You gain special insigh...","description":"<p>Spend a Slow Action to tap into the machine's databases. You gain special insight into the enemy, granting yourself a +1 to all actions taken to defeat the targeted enemy for the remainder of the combat. If the enemy is multiple of the same type, the +1 applies to them as well. Reduce your Ego by 1 at the end of your turn.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATan02","name":"Curse of the Ancients","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Ancient","excerpt":"Create an additional Side Arm upon taking this talent, it uses Empathy + Command...","description":"<p>Create an additional Side Arm upon taking this talent, it uses Empathy + Command as its pool. Damage ignores all Ego Field reduction. For every 1 you roll on your regular dice during this roll, you take a single point of damage (ignores Ego Field reduction).</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATan03","name":"Elder Sign","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Ancient","excerpt":"Once per battle before an attack is rolled, with a successful Pilot roll your Au...","description":"<p>Once per battle before an attack is rolled, with a successful Pilot roll your Automata can activate this talent. The attack fails and the attacker is pushed back into an adjacent zone. The enemy must make a mobility check to avoid falling prone.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATan04","name":"Echoes","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Ancient","excerpt":"Once per Shift, you can consult the memories of a previous pilot as a free actio...","description":"<p>Once per Shift, you can consult the memories of a previous pilot as a free action. You gain +3 in a chosen Skill you don't have any points in for the remainder of the Shift.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATan05","name":"Soul Siphon","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Ancient","excerpt":"Upon defeating an enemy, roll Pilot. For every success, you gain a Temporary poi...","description":"<p>Upon defeating an enemy, roll Pilot. For every success, you gain a Temporary point of Durability (stacks). As a Fast Action, you can bestow your Temporary Durability upon an ally within the same zone.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATan06","name":"Envoy of the Beginning","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Ancient","excerpt":"Once per battle when another player activates a Talent in the same zone as you, ...","description":"<p>Once per battle when another player activates a Talent in the same zone as you, you can declare you are using the same Talent. Automatically gain that Talent for the rest of the battle and lower your Stability by 1.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATbe01","name":"Alternate Mode [Required]","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Beast","excerpt":"Spend a Slow Action or, on a successful attack, you shift into your Alternate Mo...","description":"<p>Spend a Slow Action or, on a successful attack, you shift into your Alternate Mode. While in your Alternate Mode, you can temporarily switch 2 of your Stats for the remainder of the scene or until you switch back.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATbe02","name":"Berserker","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Beast","excerpt":"While in your Alternate Mode, with a successful Pilot roll you can reduce your E...","description":"<p>While in your Alternate Mode, with a successful Pilot roll you can reduce your Ego by 1 to shift into (or out of) your Berserking state as a Fast Action. Activating this talent does not incur Stability damage. In this state, your Ego Field is also increased by +2.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATbe03","name":"Unstoppable Force","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Beast","excerpt":"By reducing your Ego by 1, you can ignore all Zone Features for the rest of the ...","description":"<p>By reducing your Ego by 1, you can ignore all Zone Features for the rest of the scene.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATbe04","name":"Monstrous Cry","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Beast","excerpt":"When you use your Automata to Frighten, Intimidate, or Impose upon others, roll ...","description":"<p>When you use your Automata to Frighten, Intimidate, or Impose upon others, roll Empathy + Command. Each success reduces the Ego Field rating of a single enemy till the end of your next turn. For each Stunt, you can target additional enemies or increase the reduction. Reduce your Ego by 1 at end of turn.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATbe05","name":"Eyes of the Predator","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Beast","excerpt":"At the beginning of combat, use a Fast Action to choose 1 enemy to hone your kil...","description":"<p>At the beginning of combat, use a Fast Action to choose 1 enemy to hone your killer instinct on. You gain an additional success on your rolls against that enemy for the remainder of the combat. (If you fail the roll completely, you do not gain the additional success.) When you destroy that enemy, raise your Ego by 1.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATbe06","name":"Bestial Claws","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Beast","excerpt":"While in your Alternate Mode, spend a Fast Action to grow monstrous claws that r...","description":"<p>While in your Alternate Mode, spend a Fast Action to grow monstrous claws that rip through Ego Fields. You gain an additional die added to your combat rolls using your claws. Claws: Medium Damage (1), Degradation (1), Grappling (1), Melee Range (0).</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATco01","name":"Explosive","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Collateral","excerpt":"Your Automata's signature weapon has been modified with explosive results, and a...","description":"<p>Your Automata's signature weapon has been modified with explosive results, and always counts as having the Area Descriptor Tag, and the Friendly Fire Flaw Tag.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATco02","name":"Scorched Earth","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Collateral","excerpt":"Once per combat, upon successfully hitting an enemy, you can spend a Stunt to de...","description":"<p>Once per combat, upon successfully hitting an enemy, you can spend a Stunt to declare this talent. Your Automata rains down hell, scorching the entire zone in an intense fire (Intensity 8). Reduce your Ego by 1.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATco03","name":"Bring Down the House","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Collateral","excerpt":"When declaring an attack on a target in a zone you don't occupy, you may target ...","description":"<p>When declaring an attack on a target in a zone you don't occupy, you may target a structure with a Close Combat attack. If successful, the structure collapses dealing Medium Damage. Spend a Stunt to declare the zone Cluttered. Reduce your Ego by 1.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATco04","name":"Bill Me Later","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Collateral","excerpt":"When your Automata aids another through destructive means, you grant a +2 modifi...","description":"<p>When your Automata aids another through destructive means, you grant a +2 modification instead of a +1.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATco05","name":"Surprise Surprise","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Collateral","excerpt":"When targeting an enemy separated by a structure or obstacle, your Automata can ...","description":"<p>When targeting an enemy separated by a structure or obstacle, your Automata can barrel through it, destroying the obstacle and launching a Close Combat attack disregarding all Cover. Reduce your Ego by 1.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATco06","name":"Danger Close","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Collateral","excerpt":"When an Area Descriptor Tag attack from your Automata is having its damage reduc...","description":"<p>When an Area Descriptor Tag attack from your Automata is having its damage reduced by the target's Ego Field, reduce the target's Ego Field by the amount of successes on the die.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATel01","name":"Corrupted Cockpit","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Eldritch","excerpt":"While in your Automata, Horror Toxicosis still affects you but only counts as ha...","description":"<p>While in your Automata, Horror Toxicosis still affects you but only counts as having 1 Toxicity. You may also choose to fail the check without rolling. Whenever you fail a Horror Toxicosis roll, you vent the Toxicosis out in a burst, deal 3 damage to every other unit in the same zone, and recover 1 point of Ego. You also recover any Wits damage from Horror Toxicosis after a Shift in a safe place.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATel02","name":"Rapid Assimilation","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Eldritch","excerpt":"When you land the killing blow on a Horror, with a successful Pilot roll you may...","description":"<p>When you land the killing blow on a Horror, with a successful Pilot roll you may rapidly integrate the remains into your Automata. This forces everyone with sight on you to Panic. Your Automata's durability increases by 4 (up to max), and you gain an additional +1 Tag to your Signature Weapon till end of combat. Reduce your Ego by 1.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATel03","name":"Arms of Anathema","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Eldritch","excerpt":"Your Automata can sprout massive tentacles from one of its hands. When performin...","description":"<p>Your Automata can sprout massive tentacles from one of its hands. When performing a Grapple Attack you deal Medium Damage.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATel04","name":"Sense the Nightmare","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Eldritch","excerpt":"Make an Observation roll to sense a single Horror within Long Range. On success,...","description":"<p>Make an Observation roll to sense a single Horror within Long Range. On success, you know exactly where the Horror is in real time. The Horror also senses your location. Reduce your Ego by 1 at end of turn. Effect lasts till end of scene. Only one instance active at a time.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATel05","name":"Bring Forth the Nest","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Eldritch","excerpt":"You must Break a Strand to activate this Talent using a Slow Action. Target a zo...","description":"<p>You must Break a Strand to activate this Talent using a Slow Action. Target a zone and bring the Beyond into it. The zone is covered in Horror matter. While in this zone the Beyond does not afflict you. You gain +3 to Close Combat and Ranged Combat while in this zone. Beyond: Characters must roll their current Stress when entering or starting a turn in this zone. Panicking results in losing a point of Stability.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATel06","name":"Reign in Hell","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Eldritch","excerpt":"When your Automata lands the killing blow on an enemy, all other allies in the s...","description":"<p>When your Automata lands the killing blow on an enemy, all other allies in the same zone or adjacent zone gain a +1 modification to Close Combat and Ranged Combat until the end of the battle. This effect stacks up to +3.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAAThe01","name":"Heavily Armored","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Heavy","excerpt":"Your Automata's armor is incredibly dense. Your final Durability stat is increas...","description":"<p>Your Automata's armor is incredibly dense. Your final Durability stat is increased by +3.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAAThe02","name":"Portable Armory","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Heavy","excerpt":"Your Automata can deploy with 3 weapons instead of 2 (2 signature weapons and a ...","description":"<p>Your Automata can deploy with 3 weapons instead of 2 (2 signature weapons and a side weapon.) Your signature weapons are built with +4 instead of +3 in Weapon Tags.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAAThe03","name":"Defender","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Heavy","excerpt":"When an enemy targets someone in the same zone as you and your Automata, with a ...","description":"<p>When an enemy targets someone in the same zone as you and your Automata, with a successful Pilot roll you may choose for them to target you instead. This effect can be used once per round.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAAThe04","name":"Fire Everything","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Heavy","excerpt":"Your Automata can fire all of your weapons at once at a single target. Make all ...","description":"<p>Your Automata can fire all of your weapons at once at a single target. Make all attacks at once with a -2 to your dice pool on each weapon. Reduce your Ego by 1 at end of turn. This counts as both your Slow Action and Fast Action.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAAThe05","name":"Overkill","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Heavy","excerpt":"When your Automata destroys an enemy, you can choose to utterly destroy them. En...","description":"<p>When your Automata destroys an enemy, you can choose to utterly destroy them. Enemies surrounding the target are demoralized and take a -2 to their rolls till your next turn. Reduce your Ego by 1.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAAThe06","name":"Invincible","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Heavy","excerpt":"If your Durability would be reduced to 0, you may instead reduce your Ego by 1 t...","description":"<p>If your Durability would be reduced to 0, you may instead reduce your Ego by 1 to instead set your Durability to 1.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATju01","name":"Old-School Arsenal","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Junker","excerpt":"Choose one of your Automata's weapons. That weapon now has the Heavy Damage Tag ...","description":"<p>Choose one of your Automata's weapons. That weapon now has the Heavy Damage Tag and the Slow Flaw Tag.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATju02","name":"Rust-Resistant","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Junker","excerpt":"Your Automata's final Durability Stat is increased by +2, and its Ego Field is i...","description":"<p>Your Automata's final Durability Stat is increased by +2, and its Ego Field is increased by +1.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATju03","name":"Last Stand","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Junker","excerpt":"Once per encounter, when your Automata Durability drops below half (rounded up),...","description":"<p>Once per encounter, when your Automata Durability drops below half (rounded up), you can activate this talent. Increase your Close Combat, Ranged Combat, and Ego Field by +2 till the end of the encounter. Reduce your Ego by 1 at end of turn.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATju04","name":"Relic","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Junker","excerpt":"When an allied unit is in the same zone as your Automata at the start of their t...","description":"<p>When an allied unit is in the same zone as your Automata at the start of their turn, they recover 1 point of Durability.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATju05","name":"Battle-Tested","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Junker","excerpt":"When your Automata takes damage, you may decrease damage by 3 (after calculating...","description":"<p>When your Automata takes damage, you may decrease damage by 3 (after calculating Ego Field soak). Reduce your Ego by 1.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATju06","name":"Tune Up","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Junker","excerpt":"Once per battle, spend a Slow Action to add +2 in Tags to your Signature Arm til...","description":"<p>Once per battle, spend a Slow Action to add +2 in Tags to your Signature Arm till the end of the encounter. Reduce your Ego by 1 at end of turn.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATle01","name":"Hive [Required]","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Legion","excerpt":"Your Automata can control several smaller Legion Units. At the beginning of ever...","description":"<p>Your Automata can control several smaller Legion Units. At the beginning of every battle, Legion Units start attached to the central core unit. Each Legion Unit has a Durability equal to either your Strength or Agility (chosen on taking this Talent). A single Fast Action can move both Automata and Legion Units. Spend a Slow Action to attack with either the Automata or all Legion Units. You deploy with an extra Side Weapon for Legion Units and begin with up to two Legion Units. When a Legion Unit is destroyed, reduce your Ego by 1. They are replenished after a Stretch of non-combat.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATle02","name":"Swarm Tactics","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Legion","excerpt":"Increase the amount of Legion Units you can control by one. Your Legion Units ar...","description":"<p>Increase the amount of Legion Units you can control by one. Your Legion Units are unaffected by zone conditions.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATle03","name":"Defend the Queen","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Legion","excerpt":"When your Automata is targeted by a Close Combat roll, you can use a Legion Unit...","description":"<p>When your Automata is targeted by a Close Combat roll, you can use a Legion Unit in the same zone to take a Blocking action. This does not spend your Fast Action. Only 1 Blocking action can be taken against a single roll per round per Legion Unit.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATle04","name":"Unison","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Legion","excerpt":"When taking a Slow Action attack with your Automata, any Legion Units in the sam...","description":"<p>When taking a Slow Action attack with your Automata, any Legion Units in the same zone can also attack the same target, and you roll separately for both. Reduce your Ego by 1 at end of turn.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATle05","name":"Locked On","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Legion","excerpt":"Once per turn, designate who your Legion Units are tracking. Roll Pilot; on succ...","description":"<p>Once per turn, designate who your Legion Units are tracking. Roll Pilot; on success, all units attacking that enemy gain a +1 to their dice pool. Multiple Legion Units tracking the same enemy grant cumulative bonuses. Changing targets requires another Pilot roll. Tracking Legion Units cannot be used in combat.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATle06","name":"Necromancer","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Legion","excerpt":"When you destroy an enemy target, you may use your next Slow Action to raise a L...","description":"<p>When you destroy an enemy target, you may use your next Slow Action to raise a Legion Unit from its remains. You temporarily gain another Legion Unit for the rest of this encounter. Reduce your Ego by 1.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATmp01","name":"Spare Parts","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Mass Produced","excerpt":"Once per battle, if you are not currently engaged with an enemy, you can take a ...","description":"<p>Once per battle, if you are not currently engaged with an enemy, you can take a Slow Action to repair yourself. Restore your Durability by half its max value (rounded up). Reduce your Ego by 1 at end of turn.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATmp02","name":"Adaptable Armory","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Mass Produced","excerpt":"When taking this talent, choose another Signature Arm or Equipment. Once per bat...","description":"<p>When taking this talent, choose another Signature Arm or Equipment. Once per battle, by taking a Slow Action, you can pick a zone not occupied by enemies and call down your chosen Signature Arm or Equipment. To retrieve it you must be in the same zone and spend a Fast Action.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATmp03","name":"Tactical Retreat","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Mass Produced","excerpt":"When a target enters the same zone as you, you can roll Mobility. On a successfu...","description":"<p>When a target enters the same zone as you, you can roll Mobility. On a successful roll, you immediately fall back to any adjacent zone. Reduce your Ego by 1 at end of turn.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATmp04","name":"Ego Field Balancer","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Mass Produced","excerpt":"When your Automata's Ego Field suffers degradation, gain 1 or an amount equal to...","description":"<p>When your Automata's Ego Field suffers degradation, gain 1 or an amount equal to the degradation you suffered (whichever is highest) and add it as additional points of temporary Durability.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATmp05","name":"Tactical Database","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Mass Produced","excerpt":"Spend a Slow Action to access the database, roll Science. For every success you ...","description":"<p>Spend a Slow Action to access the database, roll Science. For every success you roll, you can ask a question about the encounter or enemy. Reduce your Ego by 1 at end of turn.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATmp06","name":"Eagle Eye","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Mass Produced","excerpt":"Your Automata is equipped with a variety of sensors. You gain a +2 bonus to your...","description":"<p>Your Automata is equipped with a variety of sensors. You gain a +2 bonus to your Observation skill when attempting to detect hidden enemies or objects.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAAToa01","name":"Administrator [Required]","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Operations Admin","excerpt":"You operate the supporting forces and do not use traditional weaponry or possess...","description":"<p>You operate the supporting forces and do not use traditional weaponry or possess an Ego Field. You have full communications with the other Automatas and are considered their commander and their support. Unless your character is physically present, you cannot be targeted or injured. This Talent does not count against your starting 2 talents.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAAToa02","name":"Listen Up","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Operations Admin","excerpt":"Activate as a Fast Action to intercede on your pilot's behalf; the pilot can ign...","description":"<p>Activate as a Fast Action to intercede on your pilot's behalf; the pilot can ignore a single 1 on the Stress Die. Can be activated as a reaction as long as you have not spent your Fast Action this turn.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAAToa03","name":"You Can Do This","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Operations Admin","excerpt":"As a Fast Action, raise 1 of your pilot's Ego by 1. You may only use this talent...","description":"<p>As a Fast Action, raise 1 of your pilot's Ego by 1. You may only use this talent once per round. Optional: You can choose to lower a pilot's Ego by 1 on a successful Manipulate roll.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAAToa04","name":"Stare Down the Abyss","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Operations Admin","excerpt":"When you enter into a dangerous encounter, use a Slow Action to analyze the enem...","description":"<p>When you enter into a dangerous encounter, use a Slow Action to analyze the enemy by rolling Observation. For each success rolled, you gain dice that can be spent to give additional dice to a roll of any player you command. Can only be used once per encounter.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAAToa05","name":"Order a Retreat","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Operations Admin","excerpt":"As a Slow Action, roll Command to order a full retreat. A successful roll allows...","description":"<p>As a Slow Action, roll Command to order a full retreat. A successful roll allows 1 pilot to move their Automata immediately into an adjacent zone.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAAToa06","name":"Supporting Fire","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Operations Admin","excerpt":"As a Slow Action, call a strike into any zone that is occupied or adjacent to an...","description":"<p>As a Slow Action, call a strike into any zone that is occupied or adjacent to an Automata. Your supporting fire is unable to penetrate or affect Ego Fields. Strike: Medium Damage, Area 1.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAAToa07","name":"Expose the Enemy","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Operations Admin","excerpt":"As a Slow Action, roll Manipulate to expose a weakness on a target. On a success...","description":"<p>As a Slow Action, roll Manipulate to expose a weakness on a target. On a successful roll, the target takes penalties to their Armor Damage Reduction or Ego Field equal to the number of successes. This effect lasts until the end of the round.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAAToa08","name":"Resupply","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Operations Admin","excerpt":"Once per battle, take a Slow Action to launch an ammo resupply into a zone unocc...","description":"<p>Once per battle, take a Slow Action to launch an ammo resupply into a zone unoccupied by enemies. Automata units can take a Fast Action to resupply their Signature Arm or Side Arm with full ammunition (Ammo Flaw Tag). Automata can only resupply once per battle under this effect.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATov01","name":"Danger Zone [Required]","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Overload","excerpt":"Your Automata has a special extra stat known as Heat (0 to max 5). Heat steadily...","description":"<p>Your Automata has a special extra stat known as Heat (0 to max 5). Heat steadily increases as you use other talents and depletes at 1 Heat per turn start. At 3 Heat your abilities become stronger. At 5 Heat (Meltdown), at end of turn you take 2 Durability damage. If Meltdown causes Broken state, your Automata explodes dealing Extreme Damage in same zone and Heavy Damage in surrounding zone.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATov02","name":"Beat the Heat","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Overload","excerpt":"On your turn, spend your Slow Action to properly vent your systems, reducing you...","description":"<p>On your turn, spend your Slow Action to properly vent your systems, reducing your Heat by 2 immediately. At Heat 3-5: You can also melt a nearby foe — make a Close Combat roll on any target in the same zone dealing Light Damage.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATov03","name":"Heat End","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Overload","excerpt":"On a successful grapple, generate 2 Heat to immediately inflict Heavy Damage, fo...","description":"<p>On a successful grapple, generate 2 Heat to immediately inflict Heavy Damage, focusing an explosion on their center of mass. Reduce your Ego by 1 at end of turn. At Heat 3-5: This attack now hits all enemy targets within the same zone.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATov04","name":"Pierce the Heavens","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Overload","excerpt":"When attacking an enemy using their Ego Field, generate 2 Heat. Ego Fields count...","description":"<p>When attacking an enemy using their Ego Field, generate 2 Heat. Ego Fields count only half as effective, and Ego Degradation is doubled. Reduce your Ego by 1 at end of turn. At Heat 3-5: Ego Degradation is tripled.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATov05","name":"Absolute Territory","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Overload","excerpt":"When targeted by a successful attack, generate 1 Heat and add your current level...","description":"<p>When targeted by a successful attack, generate 1 Heat and add your current level of Heat to your Ego Field. Reduce your Ego by 1 at end of turn. At Heat 3-5: You may eschew the Ego cost.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATov06","name":"The Fury","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Overload","excerpt":"By generating 2 Heat you can take an additional Slow Action. This talent can onl...","description":"<p>By generating 2 Heat you can take an additional Slow Action. This talent can only be activated once per turn. At Heat 3-5: Your additional Slow Action gets a +2 modification on your next roll.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATpr01","name":"All the Angles","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Prototype","excerpt":"On a successful Observation roll when faced with an obstacle, you take an ongoin...","description":"<p>On a successful Observation roll when faced with an obstacle, you take an ongoing +1 modification to actions made to overcome the obstacle. The next time you fail a roll, lower your Ego Field by 1. Reduce your Ego by 1 at end of turn.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATpr02","name":"Adaptive Healing","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Prototype","excerpt":"When your Automata takes damage, activate this talent to immediately regain 3 du...","description":"<p>When your Automata takes damage, activate this talent to immediately regain 3 durability (up to max). The next time you take damage, your maximum Durability is reduced by 1 for the remainder of the combat. Reduce your Ego by 1 at end of turn.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATpr03","name":"Auto-Targeting Systems","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Prototype","excerpt":"Your Automata is equipped with state-of-the-art weapon tracking software. All yo...","description":"<p>Your Automata is equipped with state-of-the-art weapon tracking software. All your weapons are treated as having an additional level of Accuracy.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATpr04","name":"Ego Terror","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Prototype","excerpt":"Activate as a Fast Action to negate a target's Ego Field temporarily. Roll your ...","description":"<p>Activate as a Fast Action to negate a target's Ego Field temporarily. Roll your maximum Ego Field against their current Ego Field. On success, their Ego Field is negated till end of your turn. On failure, your Ego Field is negated until beginning of your next turn. Reduce your Ego by 1 at end of turn.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATpr05","name":"Glitched Out","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Prototype","excerpt":"You may activate this to push any roll involving your Automata a second time. Th...","description":"<p>You may activate this to push any roll involving your Automata a second time. The next time you fail a roll, take 1 damage.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATpr06","name":"Wondrous Machinery","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Prototype","excerpt":"The first time you fail a roll in combat, you can instead use this Talent to gai...","description":"<p>The first time you fail a roll in combat, you can instead use this Talent to gain 1 success. The next time you succeed on a roll, reduce your success by 1.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATsr01","name":"Beyond Limits","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Strainer","excerpt":"You can temporarily increase any die roll or your Ego Field (for a single attack...","description":"<p>You can temporarily increase any die roll or your Ego Field (for a single attack) with a +2 modification. If you do so, gain a level of Stress. You may only activate this ability once per roll.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATsr02","name":"Panic Switch","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Strainer","excerpt":"When you Panic on a roll, if you successfully attack, you gain an additional 3 d...","description":"<p>When you Panic on a roll, if you successfully attack, you gain an additional 3 damage on your attack.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATsr03","name":"Lightning Reflexes","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Strainer","excerpt":"When targeted by a Close Combat roll, you can gain a level of Stress to take the...","description":"<p>When targeted by a Close Combat roll, you can gain a level of Stress to take the Blocking action. This does not spend your Fast Action.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATsr04","name":"Adaptive Arsenal","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Strainer","excerpt":"As a Fast Action, temporarily add Tags to your weapon (not Damage Tags). The Tag...","description":"<p>As a Fast Action, temporarily add Tags to your weapon (not Damage Tags). The Tags are removed after the next attack with that weapon. Gain Stress based on the Cost of the total added Tags at end of turn.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATsr05","name":"Rage Injection","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Strainer","excerpt":"When a Panic roll exceeds 10 or more, you can ignore the text and instead act as...","description":"<p>When a Panic roll exceeds 10 or more, you can ignore the text and instead act as if you have rolled Berserk.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATsr06","name":"Window of a Waking Mind","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Strainer","excerpt":"Make a Pilot roll by spending a Fast Action; for every success rolled ask your A...","description":"<p>Make a Pilot roll by spending a Fast Action; for every success rolled ask your Automata a single question. If they respond, take a +1 modification to rolls to carry it out for the rest of this Shift. Only activate once per Shift.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATst01","name":"Unseen Predator [Required]","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Stealth","excerpt":"Spend a Fast Action to turn invisible (as long as not currently engaged). You ga...","description":"<p>Spend a Fast Action to turn invisible (as long as not currently engaged). You gain +3 to avoid being seen while invisible and to attacks while invisible. Your Sneak Attack does not incur penalties in engaged range. You break invisibility upon taking a Combat action. Reduce your Ego by 1 at end of turn.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATst02","name":"In the Dark","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Stealth","excerpt":"Upon a successful attack, you can forgo all your Stunts (must have at least one)...","description":"<p>Upon a successful attack, you can forgo all your Stunts (must have at least one) to immediately cloak as if using Unseen Predator. Reduce your Ego by 1 at end of turn.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATst03","name":"Hunter's Instincts","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Stealth","excerpt":"You gain a +2 bonus to your Observation skill when attempting to track or locate...","description":"<p>You gain a +2 bonus to your Observation skill when attempting to track or locate your target.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATst04","name":"Antlion","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Stealth","excerpt":"When you attack an enemy unaware of your presence during an ambush, you gain a +...","description":"<p>When you attack an enemy unaware of your presence during an ambush, you gain a +3 bonus to your attack roll and may Push your combat roll for free.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATst05","name":"Quantum Leap","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Stealth","excerpt":"At the start of your turn, spend a Fast Action and choose a zone within two zone...","description":"<p>At the start of your turn, spend a Fast Action and choose a zone within two zones. You and your Automata immediately shift there ignoring any zone features or enemies in between. Reduce your Ego by 1 at end of turn.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAATst06","name":"Mirror Match","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"automata","archetype":"The Stealth","excerpt":"When using Unseen Predator, your Automata creates an almost exact duplicate of i...","description":"<p>When using Unseen Predator, your Automata creates an almost exact duplicate of itself via mobile hologram. After using Unseen Predator, until the beginning of your next turn, you apply your Mobility bonus twice to your attempts to remain unseen.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTbo01","name":"Understanding","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Bound","excerpt":"Whenever you aid someone with their trauma, gain a Strand. If their trauma is th...","description":"<p>Whenever you aid someone with their trauma, gain a Strand. If their trauma is the same as your own, gain an additional Strand.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTbo02","name":"Misery Loves Company","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Bound","excerpt":"When someone goes through emotional distress in front of you, you find sustenanc...","description":"<p>When someone goes through emotional distress in front of you, you find sustenance in their emotional toil. Reduce your Stress Level by 1, and if you had a hand in it, gain a point of Stability.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTbo03","name":"Trauma Button","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Bound","excerpt":"Whenever your past trauma gets brought up, you can increase your Strength by 2 f...","description":"<p>Whenever your past trauma gets brought up, you can increase your Strength by 2 for a single scene. If you do so, add a Stress Level.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTbo04","name":"Not Your Fault","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Bound","excerpt":"When you have the option to blame someone but choose not to, increase your Stabi...","description":"<p>When you have the option to blame someone but choose not to, increase your Stability and their Stability by 1.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTbo05","name":"I Am Vengeance","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Bound","excerpt":"Whenever you hit a Breakdown or Berserk, choose someone you blame for your pain....","description":"<p>Whenever you hit a Breakdown or Berserk, choose someone you blame for your pain. You gain +1 additional dice to destroy them. If you are successful in killing them, you may end your Breakdown or Berserk at the end of the scene.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTbo06","name":"Forget Your Face","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Bound","excerpt":"Once per session, you can choose to Break a Strand and forget the important memo...","description":"<p>Once per session, you can choose to Break a Strand and forget the important memory tied to it to Reset Your Stress Level to 0.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTem01","name":"Overindulgent","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Empty","excerpt":"You have a need for emotions, thrills, sadness, and ecstasy. Whenever you put yo...","description":"<p>You have a need for emotions, thrills, sadness, and ecstasy. Whenever you put yourself into dangerous or unfamiliar territories, gain an additional die to your pool to pursue your current need.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTem02","name":"Unfeeling","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Empty","excerpt":"You regain all your Ego after a Shift of rest instead of just 1.","description":"<p>You regain all your Ego after a Shift of rest instead of just 1.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTem03","name":"Unnerving","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Empty","excerpt":"Your lack of emotional lucidity is off-putting. Gain 2 additional dice when Mani...","description":"<p>Your lack of emotional lucidity is off-putting. Gain 2 additional dice when Manipulating others.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTem04","name":"Cold Like Ice","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Empty","excerpt":"It's hard to put you off or make you panic. Once per round, you can ignore a sin...","description":"<p>It's hard to put you off or make you panic. Once per round, you can ignore a single 1 on the Stress die you've rolled.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTem05","name":"Bad Influence","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Empty","excerpt":"When you pressure someone into making an obviously bad decision, through either ...","description":"<p>When you pressure someone into making an obviously bad decision, through either Manipulation or Command, gain a Strand on them.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTem06","name":"Deprivation","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Empty","excerpt":"You can voluntarily enter into a Breakdown. If you voluntarily enter your Breakd...","description":"<p>You can voluntarily enter into a Breakdown. If you voluntarily enter your Breakdown this way, gain a bonus die to all your rolls according to your Breakdown. At the end of the scene, you exit your Breakdown and regain a point of Stability.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTfo01","name":"Blank Space [Required]","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Forgotten","excerpt":"You begin with no Strands on any other characters. Once per session, you can dec...","description":"<p>You begin with no Strands on any other characters. Once per session, you can declare a person, place, or thing familiar to you and gain a level of Stress. You gain a +2 modification to your dice pool when attempting to interact with it for the remainder of the scene. At the end of the scene, you may ask if the declared object was substantial to your past. If yes, gain a Strand. If not, gain another level of Stress.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTfo02","name":"Future Nostalgia","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Forgotten","excerpt":"Once per scene, you can Push any roll a second time, declaring that it is hidden...","description":"<p>Once per scene, you can Push any roll a second time, declaring that it is hidden knowledge that you once knew. If you do, gain a level of Stress.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTfo03","name":"Mother Tongue","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Forgotten","excerpt":"When you enter your Berserk, your Automata begins to reveal things to you. The G...","description":"<p>When you enter your Berserk, your Automata begins to reveal things to you. The GM shares information about your lost memories, granting you a Strand connected to the information. Additionally, Refresh a Strand as well.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTfo04","name":"2's My Favorite 1","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Forgotten","excerpt":"Your Strand dice succeeds on a 2 in addition to succeeding on a 1 or a 6.","description":"<p>Your Strand dice succeeds on a 2 in addition to succeeding on a 1 or a 6.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTfo05","name":"Violence Against Nature","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Forgotten","excerpt":"When you choose to pursue your past over your own personal safety, gain a free P...","description":"<p>When you choose to pursue your past over your own personal safety, gain a free Push on your next roll (this does not incur Stress). If you suffer considerable harm because of the pursuit, gain 1 point of Ego.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTfo06","name":"Last of the Real Ones","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Forgotten","excerpt":"You may exhaust a Strand on someone to send them a message, even if they're not ...","description":"<p>You may exhaust a Strand on someone to send them a message, even if they're not in the same scene as you. This message comes as a feeling or a dream. If you use this Talent, you gain a level of Stress.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTha01","name":"Entice","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Hatred","excerpt":"You put on a calm and innocent face to those who don't know the true you. Add +2...","description":"<p>You put on a calm and innocent face to those who don't know the true you. Add +2 to your Manipulation against all those that don't have Strands with you.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTha02","name":"Let the Monster In","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Hatred","excerpt":"Whenever someone needs to rely on your skill set for a task, gain a Strand with ...","description":"<p>Whenever someone needs to rely on your skill set for a task, gain a Strand with them.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTha03","name":"Marked for the Slaughter","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Hatred","excerpt":"Whenever you Break a Strand with someone by deliberately hurting them, clear you...","description":"<p>Whenever you Break a Strand with someone by deliberately hurting them, clear your Stress Pool.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTha04","name":"All We Need is Violence","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Hatred","excerpt":"Your desire to inflict pain and violence inspires you. You gain a free Push once...","description":"<p>Your desire to inflict pain and violence inspires you. You gain a free Push once per scene/battle. If the action Pushed destroys an enemy, gain 1 Ego.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTha05","name":"Mirror Mirror","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Hatred","excerpt":"When someone hurts you using words or actions similar to your own, you may Refre...","description":"<p>When someone hurts you using words or actions similar to your own, you may Refresh a Strand with them and Raise Ego by 1 (up to Max).</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTha06","name":"Pain and Panic","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Hatred","excerpt":"Every time you panic when making an attack roll, increase your Damage by +2. Whe...","description":"<p>Every time you panic when making an attack roll, increase your Damage by +2. When you destroy an enemy, lower your Stress by 1.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPThd01","name":"Growing Pains","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Hedgehog's Dilemma","excerpt":"You may Exhaust a Strand to Push a roll instead of gaining Stress. You can activ...","description":"<p>You may Exhaust a Strand to Push a roll instead of gaining Stress. You can activate this talent once per roll in addition to pushing your roll once normally.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPThd02","name":"Self-Worth","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Hedgehog's Dilemma","excerpt":"Every time you accept someone hurting you or agree with their condescending stat...","description":"<p>Every time you accept someone hurting you or agree with their condescending statements to you, lower your Stress Level by 1.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPThd03","name":"Prickly Quills","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Hedgehog's Dilemma","excerpt":"Every time you open up and hurt someone because of it, gain a Stress Die and mak...","description":"<p>Every time you open up and hurt someone because of it, gain a Stress Die and make a Strand with them.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPThd04","name":"At Arm's Length","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Hedgehog's Dilemma","excerpt":"Every time you voluntarily Break a Strand, take an ongoing additional dice to al...","description":"<p>Every time you voluntarily Break a Strand, take an ongoing additional dice to all your rolls in this scene.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPThd05","name":"Unbreakable","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Hedgehog's Dilemma","excerpt":"When you roll for Endure, you may choose to reroll the entire roll and take the ...","description":"<p>When you roll for Endure, you may choose to reroll the entire roll and take the highest.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPThd06","name":"I Won't Fight","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Hedgehog's Dilemma","excerpt":"When faced with insurmountable odds, lower your Stability by 1 to switch your St...","description":"<p>When faced with insurmountable odds, lower your Stability by 1 to switch your Strength and Agility.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPThr01","name":"Leader","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Hyper-Responsible","excerpt":"You gain an additional die to your dice pool when rolling a Group Roll. Any time...","description":"<p>You gain an additional die to your dice pool when rolling a Group Roll. Any time you successfully lead your team to victory, Refresh a Strand.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPThr02","name":"Levelheaded","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Hyper-Responsible","excerpt":"When you stop someone from Berserking, or stop their Breakdown, take a Strand wi...","description":"<p>When you stop someone from Berserking, or stop their Breakdown, take a Strand with them.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPThr03","name":"This is My Burden","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Hyper-Responsible","excerpt":"When you're trying to go alone, and someone tries to interfere, you may Exhaust ...","description":"<p>When you're trying to go alone, and someone tries to interfere, you may Exhaust a Strand to hinder the person as if you were Breaking the Strand.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPThr04","name":"Team","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Hyper-Responsible","excerpt":"When the situation is rough and your enemy seems unbeatable, you can turn to you...","description":"<p>When the situation is rough and your enemy seems unbeatable, you can turn to your friends for aid. Add a Stress Level and Exhaust any additional Strands from any characters to aid you instead of a single character.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPThr05","name":"My Body is a Shield","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Hyper-Responsible","excerpt":"You can add a Stress Level to leap in the way and take the blow instead of someo...","description":"<p>You can add a Stress Level to leap in the way and take the blow instead of someone else. If you do, halve the damage. You can only do this once per round. If this move would leave you Broken, take a Strand with the person you're protecting.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPThr06","name":"Take Command","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Hyper-Responsible","excerpt":"Whenever your friends follow your commands directly, they add a +1 modification ...","description":"<p>Whenever your friends follow your commands directly, they add a +1 modification to their dice pools.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTis01","name":"Sugar & Spice","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Inferior Superior","excerpt":"You gain successes on 5s and 6s on Command and Manipulate rolls.","description":"<p>You gain successes on 5s and 6s on Command and Manipulate rolls.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTis02","name":"Irresistible","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Inferior Superior","excerpt":"Whenever someone attempts to Break a Strand, raise your Stress Level by 1 to neg...","description":"<p>Whenever someone attempts to Break a Strand, raise your Stress Level by 1 to negate it.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTis03","name":"Applause","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Inferior Superior","excerpt":"When you perform spectacularly, whether it be in a simple task or during battle,...","description":"<p>When you perform spectacularly, whether it be in a simple task or during battle, ask the player character around you if they are impressed. For everyone that says yes, lower your Stress Level by 1.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTis04","name":"Cracks in Armor","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Inferior Superior","excerpt":"Whenever you fail your roll in any Skill, you can voluntarily lower your Stabili...","description":"<p>Whenever you fail your roll in any Skill, you can voluntarily lower your Stability by 1 to gain an automatic success on your next roll.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTis05","name":"Don't Go","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Inferior Superior","excerpt":"When you show your vulnerability to someone you've hurt in a private moment, Ref...","description":"<p>When you show your vulnerability to someone you've hurt in a private moment, Refresh a Strand you have with them.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTis06","name":"Not to Be Outdone","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Inferior Superior","excerpt":"Gain an additional die when attempting to show off.","description":"<p>Gain an additional die when attempting to show off.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTle01","name":"Bloodline [Required]","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Legacy","excerpt":"When you create your character, designate 2-5 Characters as part of your shared ...","description":"<p>When you create your character, designate 2-5 Characters as part of your shared Bloodline. You gain three Exhausted Strands across members of your Bloodline. Whenever you resign yourself to obey a Bloodline member, clear your Stress and Refresh all Strands with them. Whenever you Break the last Strand with a Bloodline member, enter your Breakdown.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTle02","name":"My Destiny","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Legacy","excerpt":"When you engage an enemy on your own, you may deal an additional point of damage...","description":"<p>When you engage an enemy on your own, you may deal an additional point of damage on a successful attack action. If you do this, either Exhaust a Strand on a Bloodline member or raise your Stress by 1.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTle03","name":"Growing Up","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Legacy","excerpt":"Whenever you teach someone about the harsh realities of this world, gain a Stran...","description":"<p>Whenever you teach someone about the harsh realities of this world, gain a Strand with them.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTle04","name":"Coordination","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Legacy","excerpt":"Whenever you roll Observation, Command, or Infiltration with your team around, e...","description":"<p>Whenever you roll Observation, Command, or Infiltration with your team around, extra successes can be given out as additional dice on your team member's next action.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTle05","name":"Back of my Head","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Legacy","excerpt":"When your Stability hits 0, you may choose to delay your Breakdown till the end ...","description":"<p>When your Stability hits 0, you may choose to delay your Breakdown till the end of the scene/battle by Tapping a Strand you have on a member of your Bloodline.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTle06","name":"Believe","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Legacy","excerpt":"When one of your teammates fails a roll in your presence, you may gain Stress to...","description":"<p>When one of your teammates fails a roll in your presence, you may gain Stress to give them a free Push on their roll.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTma01","name":"Bio-Programming [Required]","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Manufactured","excerpt":"Your Integrity/Empathy Stat begins at 2. Whenever you defy your own agency due t...","description":"<p>Your Integrity/Empathy Stat begins at 2. Whenever you defy your own agency due to someone's will or your programming, your Stat moves right (toward Integrity 6). Whenever you share an emotional moment or violate your protocol, your Stat moves left (toward Empathy 6). At Integrity you add no Stress Die to rolls. At Empathy you incur Stress as normal. Increase your Health by 2.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTma02","name":"Combat Subroutines","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Manufactured","excerpt":"Once per scene, when committing an act of violence in accordance to the orders o...","description":"<p>Once per scene, when committing an act of violence in accordance to the orders of another, you can make a free Push on your roll.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTma03","name":"Plaything of the Body","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Manufactured","excerpt":"When you are at Empathy 3 or beyond, you become capable of feeling emotions. You...","description":"<p>When you are at Empathy 3 or beyond, you become capable of feeling emotions. You gain a bonus die to all your actions involving Empathy and can make a free push on an Empathy roll once per scene. At Empathy 6, for the rest of the scene you gain free push on all Empathy rolls, then reset to 0 and take 1 Health damage.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTma04","name":"Overclocked","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Manufactured","excerpt":"When you are at Integrity 3, once per scene you can ignore the Stress cost on a ...","description":"<p>When you are at Integrity 3, once per scene you can ignore the Stress cost on a talent or from pushing a roll. At Integrity 6, for the rest of this scene if you would roll Empathy you can instead take 1 automatic Success, then reset to 0 and take 1 Health damage.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTma05","name":"Synchronize","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Manufactured","excerpt":"When someone takes a Shift to teach you something in a relevant Skill, gain a St...","description":"<p>When someone takes a Shift to teach you something in a relevant Skill, gain a Strand with them. The next time you use that skill, you can Exhaust a Strand to roll with their Skill Rating instead of your own.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTma06","name":"Human After All","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Manufactured","excerpt":"The first time your Ego or Stability would reach 0 in a scene, it instead stays ...","description":"<p>The first time your Ego or Stability would reach 0 in a scene, it instead stays at 1.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTot01","name":"The Other Me [Required]","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Other","excerpt":"Name the Other that lives inside of your mind. You can even have Strands with th...","description":"<p>Name the Other that lives inside of your mind. You can even have Strands with them. Once per session, the GM will name a want of your Other, and you gain a bonus die to all actions in pursuing this want. If you succeed in giving it what it wants, take a Strand with them.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTot02","name":"Multifunctional","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Other","excerpt":"Your Other is adept at 1 skill, choose that skill when you take this Talent. You...","description":"<p>Your Other is adept at 1 skill, choose that skill when you take this Talent. You gain an additional 3 points in that Skill.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTot03","name":"In My Head","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Other","excerpt":"When you would take Stability or Ego loss, you can instead Exhaust a Strand with...","description":"<p>When you would take Stability or Ego loss, you can instead Exhaust a Strand with your Other to avoid the loss.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTot04","name":"They Told Me","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Other","excerpt":"When you Exhaust a Strand on someone, it will allow you to peer into their mind ...","description":"<p>When you Exhaust a Strand on someone, it will allow you to peer into their mind and realize a secret about them. If you don't have an available Strand you may instead gain 2 Stress.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTot05","name":"Save Me","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Other","excerpt":"When you choose to disobey your Other to help someone real, gain a Stress Die. R...","description":"<p>When you choose to disobey your Other to help someone real, gain a Stress Die. Reroll all ones on your next roll (not including Strand Die) to help that person.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTot06","name":"Multiple Egos","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Other","excerpt":"Your Other's Ego aids you. When you activate this move, Exhaust any number of St...","description":"<p>Your Other's Ego aids you. When you activate this move, Exhaust any number of Strands that you have with your personality. Your Ego increases by an equal amount for this scene.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTpu01","name":"Dark Secrets","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Puppeteer","excerpt":"You gain power from secrets you have over others. Every time you discover a sign...","description":"<p>You gain power from secrets you have over others. Every time you discover a significant secret about someone, gain a Strand.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTpu02","name":"Blackmail","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Puppeteer","excerpt":"Strands are bargaining chips more than they are signs of intimacy. When you Mani...","description":"<p>Strands are bargaining chips more than they are signs of intimacy. When you Manipulate or Command someone, you gain bonus dice equal to the number of Strands (not exhausted) you have with that person.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTpu03","name":"Cut the Strings","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Puppeteer","excerpt":"You don't like it when others have an up on you. When you Break a Strand with so...","description":"<p>You don't like it when others have an up on you. When you Break a Strand with someone, raise your Stability by 1.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTpu04","name":"Failing Forward","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Puppeteer","excerpt":"Even in defeat you seize victory. Whenever you fail a roll, gain an additional d...","description":"<p>Even in defeat you seize victory. Whenever you fail a roll, gain an additional dice. This additional dice expires the next time you would succeed (this effect stacks).</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTpu05","name":"Expose Them","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Puppeteer","excerpt":"You can add your Empathy to a Close Combat or Ranged Combat roll. If you do this...","description":"<p>You can add your Empathy to a Close Combat or Ranged Combat roll. If you do this, increase your Stress by 1.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTpu06","name":"Ignorance is Bliss","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Puppeteer","excerpt":"When you successfully Manipulate someone and they are none the wiser, both of yo...","description":"<p>When you successfully Manipulate someone and they are none the wiser, both of you can lower your Stress by 1.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTsh01","name":"Carry Me","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Sheltered","excerpt":"Whenever you make a Strand with someone, ask them for any request. If they oblig...","description":"<p>Whenever you make a Strand with someone, ask them for any request. If they oblige, you may both reduce your Stress Levels by 1 and gain a point of Stability (up to max).</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTsh02","name":"Open Book","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Sheltered","excerpt":"When you bear your inner feelings or insecurities to someone, Refresh a Strand w...","description":"<p>When you bear your inner feelings or insecurities to someone, Refresh a Strand with them, and reduce your Stress Level by 1.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTsh03","name":"Innocent","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Sheltered","excerpt":"When your childish and innocent nature keeps you from understanding a dark truth...","description":"<p>When your childish and innocent nature keeps you from understanding a dark truth, gain a point of Stability (up to max).</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTsh04","name":"Put on a Smile","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Sheltered","excerpt":"You may raise your Stress Level by 1 to raise your Empathy by 2 for a single sce...","description":"<p>You may raise your Stress Level by 1 to raise your Empathy by 2 for a single scene. You can only use this talent once per scene.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTsh05","name":"Break the Cutie","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Sheltered","excerpt":"When you take Stability damage, you can choose to switch your Empathy score with...","description":"<p>When you take Stability damage, you can choose to switch your Empathy score with any other Stat for a single scene.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTsh06","name":"What Dreams Are Made Of","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Sheltered","excerpt":"Whenever you're attempting to convince someone of your ideals, add a +2 modifica...","description":"<p>Whenever you're attempting to convince someone of your ideals, add a +2 modification to your dice pool.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTth01","name":"Death Drive","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Thanatos","excerpt":"Whenever an enemy harms you, reduce your Stress by 1.","description":"<p>Whenever an enemy harms you, reduce your Stress by 1.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTth02","name":"First Blood","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Thanatos","excerpt":"Whenever you harm an enemy that hasn't been harmed yet, you may double the base ...","description":"<p>Whenever you harm an enemy that hasn't been harmed yet, you may double the base damage from your attack. This can only occur once per encounter. If you do this, increase your Stress by 1.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTth03","name":"Adrenaline","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Thanatos","excerpt":"Whenever an enemy harms you, increase either Close Combat or Ranged Combat by 1 ...","description":"<p>Whenever an enemy harms you, increase either Close Combat or Ranged Combat by 1 on your next roll. This does not stack.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTth04","name":"Toughening it Out","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Thanatos","excerpt":"Whenever you reach Broken status, you may raise your Stress level by 1 to avoid ...","description":"<p>Whenever you reach Broken status, you may raise your Stress level by 1 to avoid rolling a Critical Injury.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTth05","name":"Chaos Theory","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Thanatos","excerpt":"When someone with a Strand shows concern and worries about you, Refresh a Strand...","description":"<p>When someone with a Strand shows concern and worries about you, Refresh a Strand and erase 1 point of damage.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPTth06","name":"Burn Bright","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","system":{"talentSource":"pilot","archetype":"The Thanatos","excerpt":"When Broken, you can forgo moving to make a combat roll at a nearby enemy. If yo...","description":"<p>When Broken, you can forgo moving to make a combat roll at a nearby enemy. If you do this, increase your Stress by 1.</p>","isHopeTalent":false,"isStrandTalent":false},"flags":{}}
